    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make money management lessons mandatory in schools",
        "additional_details": "All through school life you are told that your GCSE/A-level grades will prepare you for the world but this is not true. \r\nSince leaving sixth form I have had to learn how the world works, how would I buy my own house? What even is a mortgage? These are things that need to be taught and young people need to be equipped with in the real world.",
        "background": "Young children need to be able to prepare themselves for the real world once they leave school, there are no lessons provided within schools that allow this to happen. So I propose that we provide a lesson to children which focuses on \u2018general studies\u2019 this would include money management, finances.",
